{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2013}}
'''Abdul Basit Ahmad''' ({{lang-ar|'''<U+0639><U+0628><U+062F><U+0627><U+0644><U+0628><U+0627><U+0633><U+0637> <U+0623><U+062D><U+0645><U+062F>'''}}) is an author of [[Syria]]n origin residing in [[Saudi Arabia]] writing primarily about [[Sunni]] [[Islam]]. He was born in 1958 in the village of [[Dabeq]] to the north of [[Aleppo]]. He completed his elementary school education at the same village and moved to the nearby city of Aleppo where he joined the Khusruwiyah Shari'ah Secondary School from which he graduated in 1976. He completed his undergraduate studies at the Department of English Language and Literature, University of Aleppo. IN 1982, he left to Saudi Arabia to join [[Imam Muhammad ibn Saud Islamic University]] as a translator. He is still living in Saudi Arabia as of December 2010. In addition to translation, he works as an editor of Al-Da'wah Magazine published in English in Riyadh. He wrote several short books on the companions of the prophet [[Muhammad]]. These include:

==Works==
* [[Ali bin Abi Talib (R) : The Fourth Caliph of Islam]]<ref>[http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/9960717895 Amazon.com: Ali bin Abi Talib (R) : The Fourth Caliph of Islam: Books: Abdul Basit Ahmad<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>&mdash;1 January 2001, regarding [[Ali]]
* Abu Bakr As-Siddiq (R): The First Caliph of Islam<ref name="amaz">[http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/search-handle-url/index=books&field-author-exact=Abdul%20Basit%20Ahmad&rank=-relevance%2C%2Bavailability%2C-daterank/103-5856632-0740605 Amazon.com: Abdul Basit Ahmad: Books<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref>[http://simpleislam.com/Confirm.asp?id=62 Abu Bakr As-Siddiq (R)<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>&mdash;1 January 2001, regarding [[Abu Bakr]]
* Umar bin Al-Khattab (R): The Second Caliph of Islam<ref name="amaz"/>&mdash;1 March 2001, regarding [[Umar]]
* Uthman bin Affan (R): The Third Caliph of Islam<ref name="amaz"/>&mdash;1 March 2001, regarding [[Uthman]]
* Shining Stars Among the Prophets Companions<ref>[http://onlineislamicstore.com/b7897.html Shining Stars Among the Prophets Companions : 2 volume set (Abdul Basit Ahmad)<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>&mdash;May 2001, regarding the [[Sahaba]]
* Abu Ubaidah bin Al-Jarrah (R): The Nation Trustworthy<ref>http://darussalamuk.co.uk/confirm.asp?id=64, http://simpleislam.com/Confirm.asp?id=61</ref>&mdash;regarding [[Abu Ubayda ibn al-Jarrah]]
* Abdullah bin Umar: The Jurist<ref>[http://simpleislam.com/Confirm.asp?id=47 Abdullah bin Umar<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>&mdash;regarding [[Abd-Allah ibn Umar]]
* Az-Zubair bin Al-Awwam (R): The Disciple<ref>[http://simpleislam.com/confirm.asp?id=68 Az-Zubair bin Al-Awwam <!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>&mdash;regarding [[Zubayr ibn al-Awwam]]
* Amr bin Al-Aas (R): The Conqueror of Egypt<ref>[http://simpleislam.com/Confirm.asp?id=66 Amr bin Al-Aas (R)<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>&mdash;regarding [[Amr ibn al-A'as]]
* Abu Dhar Al-Gifari (R): Struggle for Equality<ref>[http://simpleislam.com/Confirm.asp?id=63 Abu Dhar Al-Gifari (R)<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>&mdash;regarding [[Abu Dharr]]
* Khabbab bin Al-Aratt (R): The Teacher<ref>[http://simpleislam.com/confirm.asp?id=77 Khabbab bin Al-Aratt (R)<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>&mdash;regarding [[Khabbab ibn al-Aratt]]
* Khalid bin Al-Waleed (R): The Sword of Allah<ref>[http://simpleislam.com/Confirm.asp?id=78 Khalid bin Al-Waleed (R)<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>&mdash;regarding [[Khalid ibn Waleed]]
* Jabir bin Abdullah (R): The Example of Sacrifice<ref>[http://simpleislam.com/confirm.asp?id=76 Jabir bin Abdullah (R)<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>&mdash;regarding [[Jabir ibn Abd-Allah]]

